PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1778691956
OL,3,CTeacher accused of murder told
OL,4,Cofficers 'I will fight you 'til the
OL,5,Cday i die'
OL,7,FThe officer asked Varley: "How do you
OL,8,Fexplain that, Jamie? He's slipped,
OL,9,Fwhimpering, I would describe him as
OL,10,Fdistressed. Why not go to comfort him?
OL,12,F"Have you left him in the bath because
OL,13,Fyou are fed up with him?"
OL,15,FVarley replied: "I was keeping an eye
OL,16,Fon him. He's not distressed. There was
OL,17,Fno intent to hurt him."
OL,26,@oD@[OUtD@AOUuD@YO]wD@QOUyD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/13
